cn:association.cn:title: European markets end on a positive note amid earnings and data; GKN slips 4.8%
cn:association.cn:summary: European equities finished in positive territory on Thursday, as investors digested the latest corporate earnings and data releases.
cn:association.cn:linkHeadline: European markets end on a positive note amid earnings and data; GKN slips 4.8%
cn:association.headline: European markets end on a positive note amid earnings and data; GKN slips 4.8%
cn:association.cn:shorterHeadline: European markets end on a positive note amid earnings
cn:association.cn:shorterDescription: European equities finished in positive territory on Thursday, as investors digested the latest corporate earnings and data.
cn:association.cn:shortestDescription: European equities finished in positive territory on Thursday, as investors digested the latest earnings and data.
cn:association.cn:bodyTeaser:
European equities finished in positive territory on Thursday, as investors digested the latest corporate earnings and data releases.

The pan-European STOXX 600 provisionally rose 0.78 percent by the market close, with almost all sectors ending the trading day in the black. Sentiment remained boosted throughout afternoon trade, as markets in the U.S. bounced back and traded higher Thursday.

Looking to bourses, the U.K.'s FTSE 100 popped 0.19 percent, while France's CAC 40 rose 0.66 percent and Germany's DAX closed up 0.55 percent.
